    <name>
				<text>10.2.3.8 Find z1^2*z2</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<p>Given \( \displaystyle{z_1= {@z1@} }\) and \(\displaystyle{z_2= {@z2@}}\) find:</p>

<li><p>\( \displaystyle z= z_1^2 z_2 = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>
<p> Write your answer in <b> Cartesian </b> form. </p>

<li><p> the modulus of \( z = \)&nbsp;[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</p></li>

<li><p>the argument of \(z = \)&nbsp;[[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]</p></li></ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given \( \displaystyle{z_1= {@z1@}} \) and \(\displaystyle{z_2= {@z2@}}\). First, convert these into the polar form:</p>
<p>We then have</p>
<p>\(\displaystyle{z_1={@r1@}\left(\cos\left({@th1@}\right)+i\sin\left({@th1@}\right)\right)}\) and&nbsp;\(\displaystyle{z_2={@r2@}\left(\cos\left({@-th2@}\right)+i\sin\left({@-th2@}\right)\right)}\). &nbsp;</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts"> <li>
 \(\displaystyle{z = z_1^2 z_2 = {@ta1_c@}}\).</li>
<li> The modulus of \(z\) is {@ta2@}.</li>
<li> The argument of \(z\) is \(\displaystyle{@ta3@}\).</li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>1.0000000</defaultgrade>
